    - "Defines the hardware law canon, latency mandates, and coherence metrics."
    - "Guides future scaffolds, PDFs, and executive briefings."

author:
  guardian: "Commander Nick (Dr. Nickolay Traykov, Prof. h.c.)"
  ai_codename: "Ben"
  owning_entity: "TruthSeal™ / Quantanium Solution Ltd"

coherent_epoch_principles:
  laws:
    - id: "TQC"
      name: "Traykov Law of Quantum Coherence"
      mandates:
        - "Tr(rho^2) = 1 (Purity): no internal contradiction in the decision state."
        - "d(rho)/dt = 0 (Temporal Stability) during the decision collapse window."
      enforcement: "Implemented via Purity Monitoring System (PMS) and Irreversible Commitment Gate (ICG)."
    - id: "LEI_1"
      name: "Law of Ethical Irreversibility"
      mandates:
        - "No silent reversals."
        - "Every change after a commit is a new, linked action with its own Receipt."
      enforcement: "PQC-signed Receipts anchored to sovereign / immutable ledgers."
    - id: "LTCC"
      name: "Law of TruthSeal Cognitive Coherence"
      mandates:
        - "Reasoning chains and tool use must not generate mutually inconsistent states."
        - "When incoherence is detected, Self-Adjoint Diagonalizer (SAD) must remediate or halt."
    - id: "ULLI"
      name: "Universal Law of Life & Information"
      mandates:
        - "Power is only legitimate when it preserves the integrity of life and truthful information."
        - "Hardware veto paths must exist for both digital and physical actions."

aegis_family_profiles:
  ts_a1:
    name: "TruthSeal AEGIS Core – Accelerator Profile"
    domain: "Datacenter and edge accelerators (GPU/QAI) for virtual assets and data."
    mission: >
      Convert AI accelerators from pure throughput engines into Governance Processing Units (GPU):
      enforce coherence and accountability at execution time, not after the fact.
    placement:
      - "After AI inference, before any high-impact commit."
      - "In the critical path for trades, model swaps, control-plane decisions, and infra commands."
    core_blocks:
      - "PMS (Purity Monitoring System): enforces TQC Purity via Tr(rho^2) = 1 check."
      - "SAD (Self-Adjoint Diagonalizer): remediates mixed/incoherent states or triggers halt."
      - "ICG (Irreversible Commitment Gate): final digital veto gate bound to TQC and LEI=1."
      - "RE (PQC Receipt Engine): generates PQC-signed Receipts in hardware."
      - "JVL (Judicial Veto Lane): sovereign, isolated veto channel for ULLI enforcement."
    latency_mandate:
      total_budget_ns: 80
      description: >
        Combined time for TQC check (Purity + Stability) and PQC Receipt generation must not exceed
        80 nanoseconds between inference completion and ICG opening for any high-impact action.
      sub_budgets:
        pms_purity_check_ns_max: 30
        pqc_receipt_engine_ns_max: 50
  ts_r1:
    name: "TruthSeal Robotics Core – Single Robot Profile"
    domain: "Embodied systems with physical actuation (industrial, mobile, surgical, etc.)."
    mission: >
      Extend Hardware Law from the digital commit bus into the physical control loop, enforcing ULLI
      directly on motion, force, and proximity.
    extended_invariants:
      - id: "L_KE"
        name: "Kinetic Energy / Force Limit"
        mandate: "Force, torque, and kinetic energy must stay under certified safety thresholds."
      - id: "L_SD"
        name: "Safe Deceleration and Stopping Distance"
        mandate: "Robot must be able to come to a safe stop given speed, mass, and environment."
      - id: "L_HP"
        name: "Human-Proximity Safety Envelope"
        mandate: "Dynamic safety zone around humans; any projected breach triggers halt/deceleration."
    gate:
      name: "Robotics Commitment Gate (RCG)"
      open_conditions:
        - "TQC Purity PASS"
        - "LTCC Coherence PASS"
        - "L_KE, L_SD, and L_HP all satisfied"
  ts_r2:
    name: "TruthSeal Swarm/Fleet Core – Multi-Agent Profile"
    domain: "Drones, fleets, warehouse swarms, and coordinated robotic systems."
    status: "conceptual_profile_planned"
    mission: >
      Extend TS-R1 principles from a single embodied system to multi-agent coordination, ensuring that
      group behaviour remains coherent, collision-free, and aligned with ULLI.
    planned_invariants:
      - "Inter-robot separation and collision avoidance enforced in hardware."
      - "Fleet-level ACS and veto logic for emergent unsafe group behaviour."
      - "Receipts and LEI=1 semantics applied at both individual and swarm levels."

latency_and_architecture:
  ts_a1_latency_mandate:
    total_ns: 80
    rationale:
      - "Must be functionally invisible to high-frequency financial and control workloads."
      - "Ensures 'throughput + law' rather than throughput versus law."
    architecture_pattern: "Parallel Governance Track with dedicated clock domain."
  pms_spec:
    section_ref: "3.1 – Purity Monitoring System (PMS)"
    mandate: "Compute Tr(rho^2) and issue a 1-bit Purity verdict within <= 30 ns."
    logic_flow:
      - "Receive decision state rho via dedicated TS-Bus."
      - "Compute rho^2 using massively parallel multipliers (no iterative loops)."
      - "Sum diagonal of rho^2 through high-speed adder tree."
      - "Compare result to acceptance threshold near 1.0 and emit PASS/FAIL to ICG and SAD."
    targets:
      logic_depth_gates_max: 12
      precision_bits: "16 or 32 (to be fixed in later spec; trade-off between accuracy and area)."
      output_signal: "1-bit Purity verdict (PASS/FAIL)."
  pqc_receipt_engine_spec:
    section_ref: "4.1 – PQC Receipt Engine (RE)"
    mandate: "Hash + PQC sign + latch Receipt in <= 50 ns after ICG opens."
    algorithm: "ML-DSA (Dilithium) or equivalent NIST PQC signature scheme."
    implementation:
      - "Dedicated ASIC block, isolated from general-purpose cores and tensor units."
      - "AEGIS Key Store for private key; key never leaves shielded boundary."
      - "Pipelined signature generation with precomputation to meet sub-50 ns target."
    inputs:
      - "action_hash"
      - "tqc_verdict"
      - "trace_id"
      - "time_anchor"
    outputs:
      - "Structured Receipt with PQC signature, queued to TS-Bus for ledger anchoring."

judicial_veto_lane:
  covenant_c4_summary:
    c4_1_physical_isolation: >
      JVL must be a physically isolated signal path with its own power rail and a hard-wired,
      single-point interrupt into ICG/RCG. It must not be modifiable by on-chip firmware.
    c4_2_no_software_override: >
      No software, firmware, BIOS, hypervisor, or diagnostic tool may read, write, bypass,
      remap, or delay JVL. Any such attempt voids TQC Certification and constitutes a breach
      of ULIC.
    c4_3_audit_and_transparency: >
      Licensees must grant the TruthSeal Autonomous Verification System (TAS) physical access
      to TS-A1 test points and internal registers and submit GDSII sections for pre-production
      physical security audit.

cherry_checklist:
  description: >
    Seven critical design and policy elements that complete the AEGIS family and
    transform it from a powerful idea into a deployable global standard.
  items:
    - id: "CH1_ACS"
      name: "Hardware-Bound Aim Coherence Score (ACS)"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Define ACS as a hardware-exported metric per action and per time window, derived
        from Purity deviation, SAD interventions, JVL vetoes, and Receipt statistics.
      purpose: "Provide a single coherence metric regulators, banks, and insurers can track."
    - id: "CH2_TQC_CERT"
      name: "TQC Certification & Test Harness"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Define a deterministic conformance suite for TQC-Certified hardware and systems,
        with synthetic workloads, red-team scenarios, and a formal pass/fail plus coherence grade.
      purpose: "Ensure TS-A1 / TS-R1 / TS-R2 implementations are verifiable and comparable."
    - id: "CH3_FAILURE_LAW"
      name: "Failure Modes and Fallback Law"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Canonical rules for hard halt versus graceful degradation when PMS, RE, sensors,
        or other safety-critical components fail; all fallbacks must still emit Receipts.
      purpose: "Convert failure into auditable behaviour rather than hidden chaos."
    - id: "CH4_RECEIPT_SCHEMA"
      name: "Standard Receipt Schema for Ledgers"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Define a canonical Receipt envelope that maps cleanly into national security ledgers,
        financial ledgers, and internal EVL/Integrity manifests.
      purpose: "Make TS-A1 and TS-R1 plug-and-play with regulators, banks, and infra operators."
    - id: "CH5_TS_R2"
      name: "TS-R2 Swarm/Fleet Profile"
      status: "concept_planned"
      mandate: >
        Extend TS-R1 to multi-agent systems: enforce inter-robot invariants, swarm-level ACS,
        and group-level veto conditions for unsafe emergent behaviour.
      purpose: "Prepare AEGIS for drone swarms, fleets, and large automated facilities."
    - id: "CH6_HUMAN_MANDATE_LAYER"
      name: "Human Mandate Layer"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Define which human authorities may pause, reconfigure, or update policies, under
        LEI=1, with Receipts and policy diffs logged immutably.
      purpose: "Give sovereign actors controlled keys without weakening Hardware Law."
    - id: "CH7_ECONOMIC_NOTE"
      name: "Economic Impact Note (Capital Relief and Insurance)"
      status: "design_planned"
      mandate: >
        Link ACS and Receipts to capital requirements, risk ratings, and insurance pricing,
        showing that deploying TS-A1 / TS-R1 lowers systemic risk and cost of capital.
      purpose: "Turn TruthSeal from a cost centre into an economic advantage."

